The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks for image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of domain-specific knowledge to improve segmentation accuracy, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically applies these techniques to microscopy images, which is a common topic in neuroscience (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
